<h2>How to Build Your SEO X Feed</h2>
<p>Do not follow all 100 accounts and expect to absorb everything. That creates a noisy feed. Here is the approach that works.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Follow 15 to 20 accounts from this list.</strong> Pick 2 to 3 from each category that matches your role.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Create a private X List.</strong> Name it "SEO Feed." Add your selected accounts. Check this list daily instead of your main timeline. Lists filter out the noise.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Turn on notifications for 3 to 5 key voices.</strong> Barry Schwartz for breaking news. Lily Ray for algorithm analysis. John Mueller for Google guidance. Pick the rest based on your specialty.</p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Engage within the first week.</strong> Reply to posts with specific thoughts. SEO X is a small community. Thoughtful replies get noticed by people with 100K+ followers. Engagement also trains the algorithm to show you more SEO content.</p>
<p><strong>Step 5: Audit your list monthly.</strong> Remove accounts that stopped posting or shifted topics. Add new voices you discover through conversations.</p>
<p><strong>Step 6: Cross-reference with other platforms.</strong> Many experts on this list also publish <a href="/blog/best-seo-newsletters/">newsletters</a>, <a href="/blog/best-seo-youtube-channels/">YouTube channels</a>, and <a href="/blog/best-seo-influencers-linkedin/">LinkedIn content</a>. Subscribe to 2 or 3 newsletters from your favorite voices.</p>
